swissarmyhammer-code-context/src/ops/get_implementations.rs vs get_hover.rs

The `file_path_to_uri` implementations handle relative paths differently:

- get_hover.rs (and get_diagnostics.rs copy): resolves relative paths via `std::env::current_dir().join(path)` producing `file:///absolute/path`
- get_implementations.rs: prepends `file:///` directly to relative paths, producing `file:///relative/path` which is an invalid file URI

The get_implementations.rs version:
```rust
fn file_path_to_uri(path: &str) -> String {
    if path.starts_with('/') {
        format!("file://{}", path)
    } else {
        format!("file:///{}", path)  // BUG: invalid URI
    }
}
```

This means get_implementations will produce invalid URIs for relative paths, causing the LSP server to fail silently or return no results.

Suggestion: Use the cwd-based resolution from get_hover.rs consistently, or better yet, resolve relative paths to workspace-root-relative absolute paths at the MCP handler layer before passing to ops."

